Athletics doping findings to be revealed
Media playback is not supported on this deviceAllegations of money laundering, bribery and doping in international athletics are all expected to feature in a report out later today, by an independent commission set up by the World Anti-Doping Agency.The president of athletics' governing body, Lord Coe, has said he was stunned by claims that officials at the highest level accepted bribes to cover up the use of drugs by Russian athletes.Richard Conway reports.